Knowledge is the holiest of the holies, the god of the gods, and commands the
respect of crowned heads; shorn of it a man is but an animal. The fixtures and
furniture of oneâ€™s house may be stolen by thieves; but knowledge, the highest
treasure, is above all stealing.
